cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.MM

The paper deals with graph-based learning, subspace clustering, and subspace learning, which are all topics related to machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of sparse similarity graphs, which are related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper uses quantitative benchmarks to evaluate the performance of the proposed method, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM).
